comment.body: I have 579 peers (on zero hello) with a closed port, tor hidden service working and on WiFi. I'm running this node and tor both on termux (a version of Linux that runs in non rooted android)
I think my port stays closed because I'm using tor as a socks proxy for the trackers. All my connection s apear to be onion connections.
Does this project have any actual software or is it just info about cloidflare and related activism?

I foeget whether or not it applies to this podcast or not but I think that Jack Dorsey is overly optimistic about AI. For instance he said that youtube knows better what I want to see than I do but my experience doesn't match this. I find that youtube is not good at suggesting current videos from the channels that I watch the most. Perhaps, what Dorsey ment to say was youtube was very good at suggesting videos that youtube wants me to see based on my relative intereat and advertiser prefferences.
